<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 13 at 9:21PM CST  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...AREAS OF FOG DEVELOPING ACROSS THE NORTHERN RANCHLANDS TONIGHT...
Areas of fog are developing across portions of the northern
ranchlands tonight. Visibilities of 1 to 3 miles in general can
be expected with these areas of fog. Locally dense fog may develop
late tonight into early Tuesday morning reducing visibilities to
a quarter of a mile or less. A Dense Fog Advisory may be needed
overnight into early Tuesday morning if visibilities drop to a
quarter of a mile across portions of the northern ranchlands.
Motorists should be aware of locally dense fog with visibility
changing rapidly over short distances. Use low beam headlights and
leave extra distance between your vehicle and others on the road.</description>
